15/02/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prosecutors announced on Wednesday (February 14th) the arrest of 11 people -- seven Bulgarians, two Germans and two Swiss nationals -- in a joint operation by the three countries' law enforcement agencies.
Officials say the ring embezzled some 7.5m euros from the EU SAPARD programme.
It is the largest such case involving EU money Bulgaria has reported.
In other news Wednesday, Bulgarian Chief Prosecutor Boris Velchev demanded that Parliament lift the immunity of deputy Toma Tomov, a member of the ruling Bulgarian Socialist Party.
Velchev wants to investigate him for suspected corruption and abuse of office while serving as regional prosecutor of Oryahovo.
(Dnevnik, Sega - 15/02/07;
Mediapool -14/02/07)
